<div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
      	
	<p n="1">
		Prosperity! Fortune!
	</p>
	
	<p n="6-7">
		27th year of the glorious Lord Rājādhirāja,<hi rend="italic">alias</hi>king Rājakesarivarman      		
	</p>
	
	<p n="1-6">
		who, ... [<foreign>meykkīrtti</foreign> of king Rājādhirāja I]
	</p>      		    		
	
	<p n="7-10">
		To whomever kingsmen of K ...
		We have given, according to the royal command <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tirumukap paṭi</foreign></supplied>, which previously had him, along with <supplied reason="subaudible">other</supplied> respected men/brahmins (<foreign>aiyariṭaiyil</foreign>), as the recipient (<foreign>peṟṟuṭaiya</foreign>) [of the endowment]
		<list>
			<item>saying <quote>We have given, as ritual (<foreign>nimittya</foreign>) provisions (<foreign>tāṉa</foreign>), for [the benefit] of all our people, to Ampalattāṭi Tirunāvukkaraiyaṉ and his lineage, who are the reciters of holy hymns (<foreign>tiruppatiyam viṇṇappam ceyum</foreign>) at/for the <foreign>tēvāram</foreign><note>discussion of the meaning of this word</note> of the monastery of the temple [dedicated to] Mahādevar in Tiruvaṭakuṭi within the Uraiyūr-kūṟṟam in Kēraḷāntaka-vaḷa-ṇāṭu [that belongs to] Kōnerimaikoṇṭāṉ</quote>;</item>
			<item>and also saying <quote>We commanded (<foreign>coṉṉām</foreign>) to take (<foreign>koḷḷa</foreign>) one tūṇi of paddy daily for the maintenance (<foreign>pōkam-āka</foreign>) of the monastery (<foreign>maṭam</foreign>) from the treasury of this god.</quote></item>
      			</list>
      		</p>
      		
      		<p n="10-11">
      			We commanded “He, the recipient (<foreign>peṟuvāṉ</foreign>), shall
      			<list>
      				<item>make the endowment (<foreign>nivantaṅkaḷ ceyyavum</foreign>) to the temple servants (<foreign>nivantakkāṟar</foreign>) who perform various services [in the temple], at the aforementioned rate (<foreign>coṉṉa-vaṇṇamē</foreign>),</item>
      				<item>rotate (<foreign>māṟṟavum</foreign>) and appoint (<foreign>iṭavum</foreign>) the endowments and the temple servants who perform different services, including the śaiva brahmins of this god.”</item>
      			</list>
      			
      		</p>
      		
